Usage: run_abstract [-help] -gds_files <string> [-gen_script_only <string>]
                    [-lib_files <string>] [-output_lef_file <string>]
                    [-run_script_only <string>] [-verilog_stub_files <string>]

-help                              # Prints out the command usage
-gds_files <string>                # List of GDSII files that need to be
                                   # translated. (string, required)
-gen_script_only <string>          # Generate just the SKILL script that can be
                                   # given to the abstract tool, but do not
                                   # execute it. (string, optional)
-lib_files <string>                # Liberty (.lib) files can also be used to
                                   # define pin directions by using the
                                   # direction from the matching .lib cell and
                                   # pin names. (string, optional)
-output_lef_file <string>          # Output lef file name that will have the
                                   # LEF macro abstracts but not technology
                                   # file information. (string, optional)
-run_script_only <string>          # Do not re-generate the script but just
                                   # execute it. (string, optional)
-verilog_stub_files <string>       # Can be used to define the pin directions
                                   # by using the direction from the matching
                                   # Verilog module and pin names.
                                   # (string, optional)